The mobile Confluence dashboard of "Popular-Blogs-Network" defaults to Popular with a list of Pages for the user to select.
However, if the Page names are consistently the same across different Spaces, for example, iOS9(space)>Setup(page) and iOS8(space)>Setup(page), the list of pages in Confluence Mobile would show two pages with the name "Setup" and would not show the name of the Parent Space in which it is related. This makes it very difficult for the user to find the info they are looking for unless they switch to Desktop version - which in mobile, especially on a phone is difficult to see and navigate.
In my opinion this just a workaround until the Confluence Mobile dashboard is completely updated to be much more mobile-user friendly for navigation and use of its features.

