I often upload newer versions of the same file. I alsways use the same file name, so they get versioned in Confluence. In every page, Confluence links every reference of a file to the very uploaded version, meaning that it points to a former version even though the file got updated in the meanwhile. This requires additional manual effort to be made to keep the page updated.

I would like to have the option to automatically update the reference in the Confluence page to always be set to the newest version of the file. That way I did not have to remove the link from the page afterwards and insert a new one.
